    <h2>Top Activities and Attractions in Japan</h2>
    <p>Japan offers an endless range of activities, from cultural exploration to modern entertainment. Here are some of the must-see and must-do experiences:</p>

    <h3>Explore Kyoto‚Äôs Historic Temples</h3>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Kinkaku-ji (Golden Pavilion):</strong> A Zen Buddhist temple covered in gold leaf, set against a serene reflecting pond.</li>
        <li><strong>Fushimi Inari Shrine:</strong> Famous for its thousands of red torii gates that lead you through a forest path up the mountain.</li>
        <li><strong>Arashiyama Bamboo Forest:</strong> A peaceful natural escape where towering bamboo stalks create a calming atmosphere.</li>
        <img src="https://img.veenaworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/All-You-Need-to-Know-about-the-Arashiyama-Bamboo-Forest-in-Kyoto-Japan.jpg" alt="Arashiyama bamboo forest" style="width: 600px; height: auto;">
    </ol>
    
    <h3>Modern Tokyo Highlights</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>teamLab Borderless:</strong> An immersive digital art museum where you walk through rooms of changing lights, projections, and interactive installations. It‚Äôs a one-of-a-kind experience blending art and technology.</li>
        <li><strong>Shibuya Crossing:</strong> The world‚Äôs busiest pedestrian crossing, where hundreds of people cross the street at the same time in the heart of Tokyo.</li>
        <li><strong>Akihabara:</strong> Tokyo‚Äôs tech and anime district, packed with shops selling electronics, video games, and anime merchandise.</li>
        <img src="https://lp-cms-production.imgix.net/features/2010/07/akihabara_lights_tokyo-fa3cbf4bacab.jpg?w=1920&auto=format&q=75" alt="Akihabara" style="width: 600px; height: auto;">
    </ul>

    <h3>World-Class Theme Parks</h3>
    <p><strong>Tokyo DisneySea:</strong> This ocean-themed Disney park is unlike any other in the world, offering beautifully designed ‚Äúports‚Äù like <strong>Mediterranean Harbor</strong> and <strong>Mysterious Island</strong>. Its storytelling and immersive environment make it an unforgettable experience for visitors of all ages.</p>
    
    <p><strong>Universal Studios Japan (USJ):</strong> Located in Osaka, USJ is famous for its attractions like <strong>Super Nintendo World</strong> and the <strong>Wizarding World of Harry Potter</strong>, making it a must-visit for fans of video games and the Harry Potter universe.</p>

    <h3>Shopping and Nightlife</h3>
    <p><strong>Don Quijote (Donki):</strong> This is a massive multi-level discount store where you can find everything from cosmetics and snacks to souvenirs and electronics. It‚Äôs a popular spot for both locals and tourists, and since it‚Äôs open 24 hours a day, you can shop whenever it suits you.</p>

    <p><strong>Shinjuku:</strong> The epicenter of Tokyo‚Äôs nightlife. From the tiny, quirky bars in <strong>Golden Gai</strong> to the neon-lit streets of <strong>Kabukicho</strong>, there‚Äôs something for everyone. Karaoke is a must-do experience in Japan, and Shinjuku is home to many lively karaoke spots. You can also visit the infamous <strong>Robot Restaurant</strong>, where robots and performers put on an eccentric, entertaining show.</p>

